name: depth-sensor-and-other-data-from-fixed-platform-and-other-platforms-from-northwest-passage-and
notes:
The accession contains microfische data provided by the Canadian
Fisheries and Oceans and taken from the Canadian Data Report of
Hydrography and Sciences. The details of the data contained in the
different microfisches are provided below:

Following are the microfische data dealing with old physical/chemical
data such as temperature and salinity data.

9000069 L105 1838 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 52. The article is from: H.J
Freeland, 1987. The article is entitled "Long Time-series of Filtered
Current Records for the B.C. Coast 1979-82". (1/1 microfiche)

9000069 L105 1838 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 51, vol 1. This article is from
Buckingham, W.R. et al. 1987. The article is entitled "Current and
sea-level measurements in northwest passage". (2/2 microfiche).

9000069 L130 1828 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 37, vol 3 (parts 1 and 2). This
article is taken from Thomas, D.J. et al., 1986. The article is entitled
"West coast data inventory and appraisal". (6/6 microfiche).

9000069 L130 1838 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 39, vol 3. This article is from
Buckingham, W.R. et al. 1987. The article is entitled "Temperature and
Salinity Measurements in the Northwest Passage". (4/4 microfiche).

9000069 L130 1838 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 39, vol 2. This article is from
Buckingham, W.R. et al. 1987. The article is entitled "Temperature and
Salinity Measurements in the Northwest Passage". (2/2 microfiche).
(PLEASE NOTE there is discrepancy in the volume number for the above
article! In prervious paragraph the same data was referred to in vol 3
and here its its cited in being in vol 2! Please check the actual data
when its online before uploading the abstract. On January 26, 2005 when
this abstract was edited by Suchira Pande the data was offline)

9000069 L130 1838 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 37, vol 2 (part 1). This
microfiche is taken from Birch, J.R. et al., 1986. The article is
entitled "West Coast Data Inventory and Appraisal". (6/6 microfiche).

9000069 L130 1838 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 5, vol 10. This microfiche is
taken from Norton, P. et al., 1987. The article is entitled "Arctic Data
Compilation and Appraisal". (5/5 microfiche).

9000069 L130 1838 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 5, vol 11. this microfiche is
taken from Wainwright P.F. et al., 1987. The article is entitled "Arctic
Data Compilation and Appraisal". (4/4 microfiche).

9000069 L130 1838 Microfiche data was taken from the Canadian Data
Report of Hydrography and Sciences no. 5, vol 9. this microfiche is
taken from Woods, S.M. and B.D. Smiley, 1987. The article is entitled
"Arctic Data Compilation and Appraisal". (5/5 microfiche).

Following are the microfische data dealing with old biological benthos
data.

9000069 L504 1838 Microfiche data taken from the Canadian Data Report of
Hydrography and Sciences no. 85. This microfiche is taken from R.O.
Brinkhurst, ed. 1987. The article is entitled "Distribution and
Abundance of Macrobenthic Infauna from the Continental Shelf off S.
Western Vancouver Island, B.C". (1/1 microfiche).

9000069 L504 1838 Microfiche data taken from the Canadian Data Report of
Hydrography and Sciences no. 84. This microfiche is taken from Burd,
B.J. et al., 1987. The article is entitled "Distribution and Abundance
of Macrobenthic Infauna from Boundary and Mud Bays near the British
Columbia / U.S. Border. (1/1 microfiche).

9000069 L504 1838 Microfiche data taken from the Canadian Data Report of
Hydrography and Sciences no. 88. This microfiche is taken from Burd,
B.J. and R.O. Brinkhurst, 1987. The article is entitled "Macrobenthic
Infauna from Hecate Strait, British Columbia. (2/2 microfiche).

Additional data submitted by the Canadian Fisheries and Oceans is filed
under NODC reference numbers L00499-L00510.
